      • wrapLong

        public static long wrapLong(long val,
                            long min,
                            long max)
        Wraps one number around two other numbers. When wrapping an overflowed number, the maximum boundary can't be the result, wheras when wrapping an underflowed number, the minimum boundary can't be the result.

        Examples:
        ValueMinMaxResult
        -1077
        0070
        7077
        8070
        -101-1
        0010
        1011
        2010
        Parameters:
        val - the value
        min - the minimum of the range
        max - the maximum of the range
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if min > max
